==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Salam
<hw>Sa*lam</hw> <pr>(s⟦adot⟧*l⟦aum⟧m")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Ar.
<ets>sal⟦amac⟧m</ets> peace, safety.]</ety> <def>A salutation or
compliment of ceremony in the east by word or act; an obeisance,
performed by bowing very low and placing the right palm on the
forehead.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>salaam</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

